---
import CallToAction from "../../components/CallToAction.astro";
import WorkCard from "../../components/WorkCard.astro";
import SiteLayout from "../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const email = "abeszilagyi@gmail.com";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Work Samples | Abraham Szilagyi"
  description="Work samples from Abraham Szilagyi: practical prototypes and proof surfaces for turning messy operational work into clearer tools."
  footerTagline="Operator-friendly systems for daily work."
>
    <main>
      <section class="section page-hero">
        <h1>Made for Daily Use</h1>
        <p>
          Focused tools like these can dramatically reduce manual work. They
          have the largest impact where tedious but unavoidable repetition
          compounds across teams, divisions, and entire organizations. When we
          understand the bottlenecks, we can create structure that lets people
          put their energy where it matters. Each tool takes aim at a specific
          kind of friction and transforms it into something easier to use. This
          approach can make an endless backlog feel like untapped possibility.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section tight">
        {/* Draft note: These three cards are the project index. Next pass should sharpen evidence and decide which supporting projects deserve dedicated pages. */}
        <div class="work-grid">
          <WorkCard
            title="Utility Work Routing Dashboard"
            sampleId="utility-dashboard"
            isActive={true}
          />
          <WorkCard
            title="Automated PDF Conversion Flow"
            sampleId="document-conversion"
          />
          <WorkCard
            title="Source-Backed Records System"
            sampleId="source-backed-records"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="work-sample-panel" data-work-sample-panel>
          <article
            class="work-sample-detail is-active"
            id="utility-dashboard-detail"
            data-work-sample-detail="utility-dashboard"
          >
            <div>
              <h2>Optimized Routes for Overhead Crews</h2>
              <p>
                The dashboard watches PDF packets that normally live in a
                SharePoint directory. Power Automate runs low-cost, targeted
                extraction on each packet, plots the jobs as markers on a map,
                and gives an operator a guided surface for selecting the work
                that is ready for dispatch. From there, they can generate,
                edit, and export an optimized route for overhead crews to
                follow.
              </p>
              <div class="button-row">
                <a
                  class="button primary"
                  href="https://green-grass-03d2f9b0f.7.azurestaticapps.net/"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                >
                  Try live demo
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article
            class="work-sample-detail"
            id="document-conversion-detail"
            data-work-sample-detail="document-conversion"
            hidden
          >
            <div>
              <h2>One Step Document Transformations</h2>
              <p>
                A backlog of pictures need to end up as PDFs ready for another
                workflow. A table buried in a work packet will be handed off as
                an Excel sheet. With the right flow, all you need to do is drag
                and drop the files into the right SharePoint folder, and the
                Power Automate flow handles the rest.
              </p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article
            class="work-sample-detail"
            id="source-backed-records-detail"
            data-work-sample-detail="source-backed-records"
            hidden
          >
            <div>
              <h2>Structured Data for Easy Navigation</h2>
              <p>
                Policies, contracts, and internal records might take weeks to
                sift through before decisions get made. This information can be
                more accessible with AI-augmented search engines. When agents
                follow a formula for organizing crucial data, with an emphasis
                on traceability, we can use everyday language to find a needle
                in a haystack. Beyond faster retrieval with cited results, the
                goal is sharper judgement through streamlined review,
                comparison, and trust.
              </p>
              <p>
                One work-in-progress example gathers technical documentation
                and research papers into a local knowledge base. Agents extract
                and review claims, entities, and relationships to map the
                landscape of relevant systems and software. The resulting
                database is inexpensive to explore while preserving accuracy
                and traceability, even with lighter models.
              </p>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <CallToAction
        title="Let's talk about what your team needs to make easier."
        buttonText="Email Me"
        copyValue={email}
        copiedText="Copied"
        secondaryHref="/"
        secondaryText="About Me"
      >
        You do not need to know the fix yet. Walk me through where the work
        gets stuck, and we can start there.
      </CallToAction>

      <script is:inline>
        (() => {
        const triggers = document.querySelectorAll("[data-work-sample-trigger]");
        const details = document.querySelectorAll("[data-work-sample-detail]");

        const setActiveSample = (sampleId, updateHash = true) => {
          triggers.forEach((trigger) => {
            const isActive = trigger.getAttribute("data-work-sample-trigger") === sampleId;
            const card = trigger.closest(".work-card");

            trigger.setAttribute("aria-pressed", isActive ? "true" : "false");
            card?.classList.toggle("is-active", isActive);
          });

          details.forEach((detail) => {
            const isActive = detail.getAttribute("data-work-sample-detail") === sampleId;

            detail.classList.toggle("is-active", isActive);
            detail.hidden = !isActive;
          });

          if (updateHash) {
            history.replaceState(null, "", `#${sampleId}`);
          }
        };

        triggers.forEach((trigger) => {
          trigger.addEventListener("click", () => {
            const sampleId = trigger.getAttribute("data-work-sample-trigger");

            if (sampleId) {
              setActiveSample(sampleId);
            }
          });
        });

        const initialSample = window.location.hash.replace("#", "");

        if ([...triggers].some((trigger) => trigger.getAttribute("data-work-sample-trigger") === initialSample)) {
          setActiveSample(initialSample, false);
        }
        })();
      </script>
    </main>
</SiteLayout>
